<subSubSection lastPageId="87" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,1231,2014]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1699,1725]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</emphasis>
At least three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1834" box="[589,687,1699,1725]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,687,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the western Atlantic have branched morphology, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro, Hajdu &amp; Custodio, 2007" authorityName="Pinheiro, Hajdu &amp; Custodio" authorityYear="2007" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="orthoreticulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina orthoreticulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pinheiro, U. S. &amp; Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R." box="[265,647,1735,1761]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref80008" refString="Pinheiro, U. S., Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R. (2007) Aplysina Nardo (Porifera, Verongida, Aplysinidae) from the Brazilian coast with description of eight new species. Zootaxa, 1609 (1), 1 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1610.1. zootaxa. 1609.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Pinheiro, Hajdu &amp; Custódio, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pallas, 1766)" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[657,979,1735,1762]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[657,817,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina fulva</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pallas, P. S." box="[830,971,1735,1762]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" refId="ref79654" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Elenchus zoophytorum sistens generum adumbrationes generaliores et specierum cognitarum succintas descriptiones, cum selectis auctorum synonymis. Fransiscum Varrentrapp, Hagae, 451 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6595" type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carter, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1036,1432,1735,1761]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cauliformis">
<emphasis box="[1036,1268,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina cauliformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carter, H." box="[1281,1424,1735,1761]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="266 - 347" refId="ref74897" refString="Carter, H. (1882) Some Sponges from the West Indies and Acapulco in the Liverpool Free Museum described, with general and classificatory Remarks. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 9, 266 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938209459039" type="journal article" year="1882">Carter, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, each of these species have particular external characteristics that allow their identification. For example, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinheiro, Hajdu &amp; Custodio" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,426,1807,1833]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="orthoreticulata">
<emphasis box="[151,426,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina orthoreticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has branches with regular diameter with a surface covered by shallow depressions, and is beige with purple spots 
<emphasis box="[418,493,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">in vivo</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pinheiro, U. S. &amp; Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R." box="[507,734,1843,1870]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref80008" refString="Pinheiro, U. S., Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R. (2007) Aplysina Nardo (Porifera, Verongida, Aplysinidae) from the Brazilian coast with description of eight new species. Zootaxa, 1609 (1), 1 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1610.1. zootaxa. 1609.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">
Pinheiro 
<emphasis box="[610,659,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[752,912,1843,1869]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[752,912,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has single or a cluster of branches with irregular diameter, repent or erect, and most commonly is ochre or brown (
<bibRefCitation author="Zea, S." box="[932,1049,1879,1905]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" refId="ref83258" refString="Zea, S. (1987) Esponjas del Caribe Colombiano. Instituto de Investigaciones Marinas - INVEMAR, Santa Marta, 283 pp." type="book" year="1987">Zea, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pinheiro, U. S. &amp; Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R." box="[1062,1290,1879,1906]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref80008" refString="Pinheiro, U. S., Hajdu, E. &amp; Custodio, M. R. (2007) Aplysina Nardo (Porifera, Verongida, Aplysinidae) from the Brazilian coast with description of eight new species. Zootaxa, 1609 (1), 1 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1610.1. zootaxa. 1609.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">
Pinheiro 
<emphasis box="[1164,1215,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[151,386,1915,1941]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cauliformis">
<emphasis box="[151,386,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina cauliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has slender and cylindrical branches with regular diameter and a finely conulose surface. A particular characteristic of the species is the purple color that is conserved after its preservation in ethanol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,1231,2014]" lastBlockId="87.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="87" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[199,434,1987,2013]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cauliformis">
<emphasis box="[199,434,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Aplysina cauliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species of the coral reefs in the GoM. Aside Triangulo Reef, we have recorded (not collected) the species in 
<collectingRegion box="[560,619,151,177]" country="Belize" name="Cayo" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Cayo</collectingRegion>
Arcas, Alacranes, and Bajos del Norte reefs. The species is also recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[180,337,187,213]" country="Mexico" name="Quintana Roo" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Quintana Roo</collectingRegion>
reefs (
<bibRefCitation author="Gomez, P. &amp; Green, G." box="[412,665,187,213]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="65 - 90" refId="ref76444" refString="Gomez, P. &amp; Green, G. (1984) Sistematica de las esponjas Marinas de Puerto Morelos, Quintana Roo, Mexico. Anales del Instituto Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, 11, 65 - 90." type="journal article" year="1984">Gómez &amp; Green 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maas-Vargas, M. G." box="[677,890,187,213]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="23 - 28" refId="ref78620" refString="Maas-Vargas, M. G. (2004) Inventario de las esponjas marinas (Porifera: Demospongiae) de la Coleccion de Referencia de bentos costeros de ECOSUR. Universidad y ciencia, 20, 23 - 28." type="journal article" year="2004">Maas-Vargas 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
